<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>We need more PvP options</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Conin_app_BCK">Conin_app_BCK</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 6:59 p.m. 9/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> We need more PvP options<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I'm sure this has happened to you before: You are talking somewhere about something and a certian person likes to butt in and let you know what they think. You have conflicting of views, and you'd like to show him a thing or two especially because he is 5 or so levels below you, but alas either he is not PvP, or you aren't PvP or both. And there is no way he would /duel you because he's afraid of you.

<P>So what do you do? many of you have played uo and i know a lot of you want to scream when i mention it, but things were so easy! you could just take them down, or get your buddies on him. Wasn't that fun? there has to be some way we can do that, without the antagonist purposly bugging people and he knows there isn't a thing you can do about it-ha ha! I really like Theblack's idea but what about the buggers who know they are safe because they aren't pvp?
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
